ples of typical objectives are as follows:

following the directions of and supporting
the lead
auditor;

preparing working documents
under the direction
of the lead auditor;

documenting
individual
audit findings;

communicating
the final audit plan to the audit
team, auditee and client;

a)
determining
the need for the audit;

cooperating
with the audit-team to permit the audit
objectives to be achieved;

report content and format, expected date of issue
and distribution
of the audit report;

